title: For Sale:  Complete Upper with BCG $400 Colt Noveske Rock River Spikes Bushmaster
postcontent:
Sorry about the hook, but I'm tired of the games...Please Read...
I just tried to buy a "Complete Upper" from a guy only to find out that the BCG is not included. When I asked him about it he said that the ad Clearly States that it doesn't come with the Bolt Carrier Group.
OK. Fair enough. It's just something I'm trying to get used to. I've built 3 ARs and on my last one, I decided to buy a complete upper.

Six months ago, when I bought a complete upper it meant that it was ready to slap on the lower and it was ready to shoot. About 1/3 still needed the rear sight but the BCG was part of a "complete" upper. Ever since the guns/parts/ammo shortage started, guys are selling "complete uppers" without the BCG. I say "guys" because complete uppers are impossible to find from dealers. But so are BCGs. You gotta be lurking on the internet all your waking hours to be lucky enough to grab a BCG from some retailer that has 20 of them for sale.And not only that but the BCGs are selling for $300-$500.  If you don't make the purchase within 30 minutes, they are sold out. It's just frustrating to see a "complete upper" for sale that is useless with out the BCG. Sure it clearly states the BCG is missing, but I betcha there are a few new guys in the game that don't catch that. They get their complete upper only to find out it is not complete. And their AR Build is put on hold indefinately. And the new guys, the guys we are supposed to be helping, has almost no possible way to get a BCG. About the only thing he'll get is an education. Come on people. Is this about the all mighty dollar? Or are we better than that?

If we don't start standing together...we're finished.

In short, Magpul would be unable to remain in business as a CO company, and the over 200 jobs for direct employees and nearly 700 jobs at our subcontractors and suppliers would pick up and leave CO.
